contentrichtext.text: {{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} [[Image:map queens chapel.jpg|thumb|right|Map of Washington, D.C., with Queens Chapel highlighted in red]] '''Queens Chapel''' is a residential neighborhood on the northeastern edge of [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]], bounded by Galloway Street NE to the south, Eastern Avenue to the east, South Dakota Avenue to the west, and Riggs Road to the north. It was named for early landowner Mr. Queen. The neighborhood is close to [[The Catholic University of America]]. {{Neighborhoods in Washington, D.C.}} {{coord|38.9546|-76.9974|display=title}} [[Category:Neighborhoods in Washington, D.C.]] {{WashingtonDC-geo-stub}}
